%N A391468 Number of words of length 3n formed with 3 types of letter where the number of each type == 0 (mod 3).
%C A391468 Among all 3*n words, the number of letters of each type can be taken in 4 cases: all of the form 3*k, all 3*k+1, all 3*k+2, or one each 3*k, 3*k+1, 3*k+2; for total a(n) + A391469(n) + A391470(n) + 2*A013733(n-1) = 3^(3*n).
%H A391468 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A391468/b391468.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..700</a> (first 101 terms from Pablo Serra)
%H A391468 Pablo Serra, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2512.22362">On the number of words of N = 3*M letters with a three-letter alphabet</a>, arXiv:2512.22362 [math.CO], 2025.
%H A391468 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (27,-27,729).
%F A391468 a(n) = Sum_{n1+n2+n3=n} trinomial(3*n; 3*n1, 3*n2, 3*n3).
%F A391468 a(n) = 3^(3*n-2) + (1 + (-1)^n)*i^n*3^((3*n-2)/2) for n>=1, where i is the imaginary unit.
%F A391468 a(n) = 27*(a(n-1) - a(n-2) + 27*a(n-3)), for n >= 4.
%F A391468 G.f.: (162*x^3-9*x^2+24*x-1)/((27*x-1)*(27*x^2+1)).
%F A391468 E.g.f.: (2 + exp(27*x) + 6*cos(3*sqrt(3)*x))/9. - _Stefano Spezia_, Dec 30 2025
%e A391468 For n=1, the a(1) = 3 words are AAA, BBB, and CCC.
%e A391468 For n=2, there are 3 single letter words XXXXXX, and binomial(6,3)=20 ways to inter-mingle XXX and YYY followed by 3 choices of the omitted type so a(2) = 3 + 3*20 = 63.
